{"abstract": "The 81-year-old Power and Light Building in Kansas City is no longer viable as office space, but some developers say it has potential as apartments or a hotel.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/04/realestate/commercial/kansas-citys-power-and-light-building-awaits-new-role.html", "snippet": "The 81-year-old Power and Light Building in Kansas City is no longer viable as office space, but some developers say it has potential as apartments or a hotel.", "lead_paragraph": "KANSAS CITY, Mo. \u2014 The Kansas City Power and Light Building is a widely celebrated Art Deco skyscraper that instantly became a city landmark when it opened 81 years ago. The 30-story building stood as Missouri\u2019s tallest for 40 years, and its six-story lantern tower, enclosed in sunburst windows and topped by a steel-framed glass cupola, still cuts a distinctive profile on the downtown skyline.", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "4", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "xlarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/07/04/business/Kansascity1/Kansascity1-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "height": 350, "width": 600, "subType": "xlarge", "crop_name": "articleLarge", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2012/07/04/business/Kansascity1/Kansascity1-articleLarge-v2.jpg", "xlargewidth": 600, "xlargeheight": 350}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/07/04/business/Kansascity1/Kansascity1-jumbo.jpg", "height": 700, "width": 1024, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/07/04/business/Kansascity1/Kansascity1-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 1400, "width": 2048, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbLarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/07/04/business/